The President made remarks at the Indianapolis International Airport regarding a recent shooting at a synagogue in Pittsburgh. He expressed his condolences and stated that it appears to be an anti-Semitic crime. The FBI and local officials are investigating the incident, and more information will be provided in the next hour. The President also mentioned speaking with the Governor and Mayor of Pittsburgh, who are both devastated by the tragedy. The crime scene is described as one of the worst that professionals have seen. The President plans to address the incident further in his remarks.